<br>
How is that not legislating morality?  From my observation right wing conservatives, Republicans (whatever they want to be called) are the ones pushing for limiting rights and choices.  Gay marriage and abortion to name two hot button issues.<br>
<br>
And please quit throwing this &quot;he said, she said&quot; line back and forth about how &quot;everyone is a hypocrite&quot; or &quot;democrats legislate morality too&quot;.  If you want to have the debate about whether or not there are two different parties, or just one in this country please start another thread.  Otherwise defend your position.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>It's still a non sequitur. Capital punishment seldom interferes with peoples lives, unless of course you commit a crime for which capital punishment is recommended. Republicans are also for those things, but to a larger degree the party is more focussed on the cost of government since getting government out of people's pockets would also reduce government interference in our lives.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
