Well I guess we stopped italicizing then? :P  Capital punishment interferes in the most extreme way possible with people's lives.  Innocent people have been murdered, there is no question about that.  Whether or not you think that tossing out a few good apples with the bad is acceptable or not I leave to you.<br>
<br>
And as far as the cost of an execution vs life imprisonment, your attitude is typical of someone that has never bothered to do research on the subject.  Look up the numbers sometime and they may surprise you.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>As far as schools go, I think the Republicans currently favor vouchers which would increase the competition and force public schools to perform better. The voucher system is also popular amongst inner city people.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
